Which of the following protocol uses magnetic field induction to enable communication between 2 electronic devices?

LTE-Advanced :       standard for mobile communication that provides enhancement to LTE thus focusing on providing higher capacity
                     in terms of data rate, extended range, efficiency and performance.

Multimedia over Coax Alliance (MoCA) : type of network protocol that provides a high definition video of home and content related to it
                                       over existing coaxial cable. (wired communication protocol)

Near Field Communication (NFC) :      uses magnetic field induction to enable communication between 2 electronic devices

Ha-Low  :      Another variant of Wi-Fi standard that provides extended range, making it useful for communications in rural areas.
               It offers low data rates, thus reducing power and cost for transmission.

