Out of the following RFCrack commands, which command is used by an attacker to perform jamming?

Attackers use the RFCrack tool to obtain the rolling code sent by the victim to unlock a vehicle
 and later use the same code for unlocking and stealing the vehicle.
 RFCrack is used for testing RF communications between any physical device that communicates over sub Ghz frequencies.
 It is used along with the combination of hardware such as yardsticks to jam, replay and sniff the signal coming from the sender.

Jamming:
python RFCrack.py -j -F 314000000

Rolling Code:
python RFCrack.py -r -M MOD_2FSK -F 314350000

Live Replay:
python RFCrack.py -i

Adjust RSSI Range:
python RFCrack.py -r -U "-75" -L "-5" -M MOD_2FSK -F 314350000


