Which of the following TCP/UDP port is used by the infected devices to spread malicious files to other devices in the network?


Port 23 : TCP port 23 is used for Telnet Services.

Port 53 : TCP/UDP port 53 is used for DNS services.

Port 48101 : TCP/UDP port 48101 is used by the infected devices to spread malicious files to the other devices in the network.
             Monitor traffic on port 48101 as the infected devices attempt to spread the malicious file using port 48101

Port 22 : TCP port 22 is used for SSH services

